  // ── Doc 27: Pricing Strategy Review ──
  createDocInFolder("Pricing Strategy Review", [
    "# RavenStack Pricing Strategy Review",
    "",
    "Authors: Sarah Chen (VP Product), Marcus Rivera (Product Strategy)",
    "Date: November 2025",
    "Status: Under Review — Recommendations pending exec team approval",
    "Reviewed by: Alex Park (CEO), David Kim (Sales Lead)",
    "",
    "## Purpose",
    "",
    "This document reviews RavenStack's current pricing structure in light of three developments: the Q4 2025 churn spike (251 events, with pricing and budget collectively driving 33% of all churn), the competitive landscape (AcmeSaaS at $279/seat, NimbusApp at $99/seat), and the upcoming AI feature GA launches. The goal is to recommend pricing adjustments that reduce churn, improve competitive positioning, and capture the value of AI features.",
    "",
    "## Current Pricing",
    "",
    "- Basic: $29/seat/month (168 accounts, $144,305 MRR in December)",
    "- Pro: $79/seat/month (178 accounts, $476,427 MRR in December)",
    "- Enterprise: $199/seat/month (154 accounts, $1,652,695 MRR in December)",
    "- Annual billing: 20% discount (annual Basic: $23.20/seat/month, Pro: $63.20, Enterprise: $159.20)",
    "",
    "Average MRR per account by tier:",
    "- Basic: $859/account (implies ~30 seats average, which likely includes some multi-team deployments)",
    "- Pro: $2,676/account (implies ~34 seats average)",
    "- Enterprise: $10,732/account (implies ~54 seats average — our largest deployments)",
    "",
    "## Revenue Analysis",
    "",
    "December 2025 MRR breakdown by tier demonstrates heavy Enterprise concentration:",
    "- Basic: $144,305 (6.3% of total) — 168 accounts",
    "- Pro: $476,427 (21.0%) — 178 accounts",
    "- Enterprise: $1,652,695 (72.7%) — 154 accounts",
    "- Total: $2,273,427",
    "",
    "Enterprise dominance has been consistent: 74% in December 2024 and 73% in December 2025. The absolute numbers are dramatically different ($207,159 vs $1,652,695), but the proportional mix is stable. This means all tiers are growing at similar rates — Enterprise is not crowding out Basic and Pro.",
    "",
    "Revenue per tier over 2025 (January to December):",
    "- Basic grew from $20,273 to $144,305 (7.1x)",
    "- Pro grew from $46,550 to $476,427 (10.2x)",
    "- Enterprise grew from $206,363 to $1,652,695 (8.0x)",
    "",
    "Pro tier had the fastest growth rate (10.2x), likely driven by Basic-to-Pro upgrades. Of 529 total upgrade events across all subscriptions, we estimate approximately 60% were Basic-to-Pro transitions.",
    "",
    "## Competitive Pricing Analysis",
    "",
    "### Direct Competitors",
    "",
    "AcmeSaaS:",
    "- Basic: $49/seat/month (69% higher than our $29)",
    "- Pro: $149/seat/month (89% higher than our $79)",
    "- Enterprise: $279/seat/month (40% higher than our $199)",
    "- Annual discount: 15% (vs our 20%)",
    "- AcmeSaaS's higher pricing is justified by: GA AI features, SOC 2/HIPAA/ISO 27001 certifications, and a native mobile app with 4.7 stars. Their premium positions them as the 'safe choice' for regulated industries.",
    "",
    "NimbusApp:",
    "- Single tier: $99/seat/month (no Basic entry point, no Enterprise premium)",
    "- No annual discount",
    "- NimbusApp's single tier limits their addressable market. They cannot land small teams at a low price point or charge premium for enterprise features. Our tiered model gives us strategic flexibility they lack.",
    "",
    "### Broader Market",
    "- Monday.com: $9-$24/seat/month (lower-end, but less capable)",
    "- Asana: $11-$25/seat/month (similar to Monday.com)",
    "- Notion: $10-$18/seat/month (document-focused, not a direct competitor)",
    "- Jira: $8-$16/seat/month (engineering-only, no collaboration features)",
    "",
    "RavenStack sits in the premium tier alongside AcmeSaaS. Our pricing is competitive at every tier and offers a strong value proposition — 40 features including 5 AI features for less than AcmeSaaS charges.",
    "",
    "## Churn x Pricing Analysis",
    "",
    "Pricing and budget are the #2 and #3 churn reasons respectively (after features):",
    "",
    "- Pricing-related churn (all time): 91 events (15% of 600 total). Customers explicitly citing price as the reason for leaving.",
    "- Budget-related churn (all time): 104 events (17%). Customers who see value but cannot afford the current price (often due to company-wide budget cuts).",
    "- Combined pricing + budget churn: 195 events (33%). This is the largest combined churn category.",
    "",
    "Q4 2025 breakdown: pricing (33 events) + budget (47 events) = 80 events out of 251 total (32%).",
    "",
    "This suggests a meaningful segment of customers who experience value from RavenStack but face affordability barriers. These are not customers who think the product is overpriced — they are customers who face external budget constraints. The distinction matters for our response: we should not lower our core pricing (which would devalue the product), but we should offer more flexible payment options.",
    "",
    "### Churn by Tier (Estimated)",
    "- Basic tier accounts churn at the highest rate (~35% of pricing+budget churn events). These are price-sensitive customers for whom $29/seat is still significant. Many are teams of 5-10 at early-stage startups.",
    "- Pro tier accounts contribute ~40% of pricing+budget churn. The $79 price point is a significant jump from Basic, and teams that do not use enough Pro-only features feel the step-up is not justified.",
