    "",
    "## Pricing Options Under Consideration",
    "",
    "### Option A: Starter Tier ($15/seat/month)",
    "",
    "A new tier below Basic with a subset of features (5-7 core features: Document Editor, File Sharing, Real-time Chat, Kanban Board, and Inbox Zero).",
    "",
    "Pros:",
    "- Captures price-sensitive customers who currently churn from Basic",
    "- Provides an even lower entry point for land-and-expand strategy",
    "- Competitive with Monday.com and Asana pricing",
    "",
    "Cons:",
    "- Risk of cannibalizing Basic tier — some current Basic customers may downgrade to save money",
    "- Adds complexity to our pricing page and sales conversations",
    "- Support cost per dollar of revenue increases (Starter customers need similar support to Basic but generate half the revenue)",
    "",
    "Estimated impact: Capture 50-100 new accounts per year that currently choose Monday.com or Asana due to price. Reduce Basic-tier pricing churn by 20%. Risk: 10-15% of current Basic accounts downgrade, offsetting gains.",
    "",
    "### Option B: Usage-Based Component",
    "",
    "Add a usage-based component to pricing. Base platform fee ($20/seat/month) plus per-feature add-ons ($5-$15 each).",
    "",
    "Pros:",
    "- Matches budget-constrained customers who only need a few features",
    "- Enables premium pricing for high-value features (AI features could be $15/seat/month add-on)",
    "",
    "Cons:",
    "- Complexity: customers cannot predict their monthly bill",
    "- Revenue unpredictability for our planning",
    "- Sales friction: harder to quote Enterprise deals with variable pricing",
    "- Industry trend: most B2B SaaS is moving toward flat-rate, not usage-based",
    "",
    "Estimated impact: Not recommended at this time. The operational complexity outweighs the benefits for our current scale.",
    "",
    "### Option C: Enhanced Annual Discount (Recommended for Q1 2026)",
    "",
    "Increase annual billing discount from 20% to 30%. This translates to:",
    "- Annual Basic: $20.30/seat/month (vs current $23.20)",
    "- Annual Pro: $55.30/seat/month (vs current $63.20)",
    "- Annual Enterprise: $139.30/seat/month (vs current $159.20)",
    "",
    "Pros:",
    "- Lock in 12-month commitment, which directly reduces month-to-month churn",
    "- Easy to implement (pricing infrastructure change only, no new features needed)",
    "- Does not devalue the product — the published price stays the same, but loyal customers are rewarded",
    "- The 529 upgrade events and 218 downgrade events suggest customers are actively optimizing their spend — a stronger annual incentive stabilizes this behavior",
