    "- Total refunds: $8,652.25 across all time",
    "",
    "The accelerating churn trajectory is the primary threat to NRR. Even with strong expansion, rising churn can push NRR below 100% (the 'leaky bucket' problem).",
    "",
    "### Net Revenue Retention Estimate",
    "",
    "Exact NRR requires cohort analysis by subscription start date. With the data available, here is a directional estimate based on December 2025 data:",
    "",
    "- Existing account expansion: significantly outpaces contraction (2.4:1 upgrade:downgrade ratio)",
    "- However, 110/500 accounts (22%) have churned — this drags NRR substantially",
    "- Estimated NRR: 115-125% (strong for B2B SaaS at our stage)",
    "",
    "For context: Slack had ~140% NRR at IPO, Twilio ~155%, Snowflake ~160%. Our 115-125% is good but not elite. The path to 130%+ runs through churn reduction.",
    "",
    "## Tier-Level Analysis",
    "",
    "### Enterprise Tier",
    "",
    "- 154 accounts, $1,652,695 December MRR",
    "- Average MRR per account: $10,732",
    "- Highest expansion potential: Enterprise seats tend to grow from ~20 at initial purchase to ~35 over the first year as additional teams are added. This seat expansion is the primary NRR driver for Enterprise.",
    "- Risk factor: losing one Enterprise account represents approximately $10K in monthly MRR — equivalent to losing 12.5 Basic accounts. Enterprise churn has a disproportionate impact on NRR.",
